    "created_at": "2023-04-30T07:37:34Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-04-30T07:37:34Z",
    "body": "> Are you aware, that you can already enable and disable modules through the command line–like `starship config kubernetes.disabled false`?\r\n\r\nHow would that help with this feature request? Or could this somehow be integrated in the shell configuration? This would be awesome, if you could provide some insight. \r\n\r\n\"show on command\" dynamically shows modules based on the command I'm just typing, so the `aws` module would only appear after I started typing an AWS-CLI command. \r\n\r\nFor me this would also be the only missing piece in starship, also coming from p10k, but I also know that's it's non-trivial to build. \r\n\r\n",
